definition.value: A 1-O-(alk-1-enyl)-2-O-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alkenyl group has Z geochemistry.
A 1-O-(alk-1-enyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alkenyl group has Z geochemistry.
A  1-O-(alk-1-enyl)-2-O-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alk-1-enyl and acyl groups are specified as (1Z)-hexadecenyl and arachidonoyl respectively.
A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alk-1-enyl group has Z geochemistry.
A 1-O-(alk-1-enyl)-2-palmitoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alk-1-enyl group has Z geochemistry.

An oxazinoquinolone carrying carboxy, fluoro, methyl and 4-methylpiperazino substituents. A synthetic fluoroquinolone antibacterial agent, it inhibits the supercoiling activity of bacterial DNA gyrase, halting DNA replication.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as palmitoyl and 8-epi-prostaglandin F2alpha respectively.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as stearoyl and 8-epi-prostaglandin F2alpha respectively.
A 1-alkyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate in which the alkyl and acyl groups are specified as palmityl (hexadecyl) and arachidonoyl respectively.
A 1-alkyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate in which the alkyl and acyl groups are specified as palmityl (hexadecyl) and oleoyl respectively.
A branched-chain saturated fatty acid comprising dodecanoic (lauric) acid substituted at position 11 by a methyl group.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the 1-acyl group is specified as palmitoyl.
A glycosylglucose in which two alpha-D-glucose residues are linked (1->2).
A branched alkane that is undecane substituted at positions 2 and 5 by methyl groups.
A hydrate that is the monohydrate form of 1-butyl-N-(2,6-dimethylphenyl)piperidine-2-carboxamide hydrochloride.
The monohydrate form of levobupivacaine hydrochloride. A piperidinecarboxamide-based local anaesthetic, it has a slow onset and long duration of action.
The monohydrate form of dextrobupivacaine hydrochloride.
A branched alkane that is heptane carrying two methyl groups each at positions 2 and 6, and one methyl group at position 4.
A branched alkane that is pentadecane carrying four methyl groups at at positions 2, 4, 6 and 10.
A zirconium coordination entity comprising four chlorine atoms bound to a central zirconium atom.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-tosufloxacin.

A 1,8-naphthyridine derivative that is 4-oxo-1,4-dihydro-1,8-naphthyridine-3-carboxylic acid bearing additional 2,4-difluorophenyl, fluoro and 3-aminopyrrolidin-1-yl substituents at positions 1, 6 and 7 respectively.
A 7-(3-aminopyrrolidin-1-yl)-1-(2,4-difluorophenyl)-6-fluoro-4-oxo-1,4-dihydro-1,8-naphthyridine-3-carboxylic acid that is the (S)-enantiomer of tosufloxacin.
A 7-(3-aminopyrrolidin-1-yl)-1-(2,4-difluorophenyl)-6-fluoro-4-oxo-1,4-dihydro-1,8-naphthyridine-3-carboxylic acid that is the (R)-enantiomer of tosufloxacin.
A hydrate that is the monohydrate form of (S)-tosufloxacin tosylate.
A hydrate that is the monohydrate form of (S)-tosufloxacin tosylate.
A glycerophosphocholine that is sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine bearing a single alk-1-enyl substituent at an unspecified position.
A 1,3-diglyceride obtained by the formal acylation of positions 1 and 3 of glycerol by hexadecanoic (palmitic) acid.
A calcium salt composed of calcium and phosphate/diphosphate ions; present in milk and used for the mineralisation of calcified tissues.
A macrolide antibiotic that is biosynthesised by Streptomyces venezuelae.
A twelve-membered macrolide antibiotic that is biosynthesised by Streptomyces venezuelae.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups at position 1 and 2 are specified as arachidonoyl and palmitoyl respectively.
A 1-acyl-2-alkyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl and alkyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified respectively as arachidonoyl and palmityl.
A 2-alkyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alkyl group is specified as hexadecyl.
An inorganic sodium salt that is the monosodium salt of arsenic acid.
A 1-O-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl group is specified as capryl (decanoyl).
An inorganic nitrate salt having Cd(2+) as the counterion.
A  macrolide antibiotic that was originally isolated from the culture broths of Streptomyces hygroscopicus var. ossamyceticus.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which 1 and 2-acyl groups are specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl) and (10E)-9-hydroperoxyoctadecenoyl respectively.

A member of the class of syringomycins that has 3-hydroxydodecanoyl as the fatty acyl tail group. It is isolated from Pseudomonas syringae pv. syringae and exhibits phytotoxic and antifungal properties.
An inorganic sodium salt having selenide as the counterion.
An inorganic sodium salt having selenate as the counterion.

A sulfonamide that is sulfanilamide in which the sulfonamide nitrogen is substituted by a 1-phenyl-1H-pyrazol-5-yl group. It is a selective inhibitor of cytochrome P450 (CYP) 2C9 isozyme, and antibacterial agent.
1-(2,4-difluorophenyl)-6-fluoro-7-(3-methylpiperazin-1-yl)-4-oxo-1,4-dihydroquinoline-3-carboxylic acid that has R configuration.
1-(2,4-difluorophenyl)-6-fluoro-7-(3-methylpiperazin-1-yl)-4-oxo-1,4-dihydroquinoline-3-carboxylic acid that has S configuration.
A quinolone that is 4-oxo-1,4-dihydroquinoline-3-carboxylic acid which is substituted at positions 1, 6, and 7 by 2,4-difluorophenyl, fluorine, and 3-methylpiperazin-1-yl groups, respectively.
An aldehydic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 9-oxononanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
